<p>CANC&Uacute;N HOTELS</strong><br>
  Whether it's business or pleasure, visitors can count on more than 140 hotels with 26,194 rooms to suit every taste and budget. Twenty percent of all properties in the Hotel Zone are Gran Turismo or deluxe, Mexico's highest service category, exceeding even five-star standards. There are luxurious beachfront properties, all-inclusive resorts, family oriented hotels, conference and golf resorts, and private condominiums. <br>
  Downtown Canc&uacute;n also has a number of hotels, some with beach clubs.
</p>
</p>
<p align="justify"><strong>Architecture</strong><br>
Canc&uacute;n's sleek skyline showcases the imaginative work of renowned Mexican architects. Architectural styles reflect an array of influences: the ancient Maya, futuristic glass pyramids, the Mediterranean, Spanish Colonial, romanesque, neo-classic, the Caribbean and the 21st century. Lobby atriums hung with vines, indoor jungles, marble floors and rich woods accent the interiors of these megaresorts, while the facades and grounds are set with lush tropical gardens and waterfalls worthy of the wild. </p>
<p align="justify"><strong>Services</strong><br>
Sterling service, world-class chefs, and bilingual staff personify Canc&uacute;n's hotels and resorts. Standard services for luxury hotels include giant pools with swim-up bars and waterfalls, tennis courts, spas, fitness gyms, beauty parlors, boutiques, restaurants, kids' clubs, watersports facilities, travel and car rental agencies, nightclubs and even mini supermarkets. Basic amenities are air-conditioning, sweeping views, color TVs and room safes. Most big hotels have meeting space, while a select few specialize in conventions offering specially trained staff and state-of-the-art audio visual equipment. Some hotels are all-inclusive, programs include unlimited food, drink, watersports and entertainment. Other options include fully equipped condos and villas which rent by the week or month. </p>
